The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | ITC profit rises 22%
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      ITC profit rises 22%
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                                            
	Calcutta, July 22: ITC today posted a 21.8 per cent jump in net profit for the quarter ended June 30, while net income rose 16 per cent.        
	The tobacco-to-hotels conglomerates net profit stood at Rs 1,070.3 crore compared with Rs 878.70 crore in the June quarter of 2009 on the back of a good show by cigarettes and paper. During the quarter, net income rose to Rs 4,847.34 crore from Rs 4,197.82 crore in the same period of the previous fiscal.        
	The company said its non-cigarette FMCG and agri-business performed strongly during the quarter. The hotel segment also looked up.        
	Revenue from the cigarette business grew 12 per cent to Rs 2,483.62 crore. Income from the non-cigarette FMCG division, including the packaged food segment and personal care products, was up 32.2 per cent at Rs 1,001.38 crore.        
	The non-cigarette FMCG business also managed to cut losses to Rs 89 crore in the first quarter of this fiscal from Rs 99 crore in the year-ago period.        
	Revenue from the groups hotel division grew 21 per cent to Rs 209.92 crore, while the agri-business grew 44 per cent to Rs 1,349.8 crore.        
	The ITC scrip rose 4.80 points, or 1.64 per cent, to close at Rs 297.60 points on the BSE today.        
	Dr Reddys net dips        
	Pharmaceutical company Dr Reddys Laboratories today said its consolidated net profit declined 14.28 per cent to Rs 209.55 crore for the first quarter ended June 30 over the same period in the previous fiscal.        
	Net income from sales and services stood at Rs 1,683.13 crore compared with Rs 1,818.94 crore in the same period of the corresponding fiscal.                                                                                                                                       
